						<p>The more widely distributed the better. Concentrating resources or power within the US is not good for us or for anyone else. I like the thought that private regulation could become more significant than state regulation. That is, the interlocking contractual arrangements between owners of key pieces of infrastructure (e.g., mining pools, exchanges) will be more important than local money transmitter licensing in some random province.</p>
